other_tests.findings: Anterior and anteroseptal wall hypokinesis, ejection fraction calculated at 56%, large anterior and anteroseptal area of late gadolinium enhancement, anterior hyperintensity due to myocardial edema.
Two discrete areas of late gadolinium enhancement, more intense anterior lesion compared to inferior lesion, inferior hyperintensity indicating myocardial edema.
other_tests.changes_over_time: The infarction in the inferior wall is acute, while the anterior wall infarction is likely chronic.
